Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.To make the potatoes, melt the butter with the olive oil in a large frying pan.Add the rosemary, garlic and potatoes, toss together and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Place in the oven and roast for 15 minutes.To make the dressing, place all of the dressing ingredients into a hand blender, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and blend together.Serve the potatoes in a warm bowl and spoon over the dressing.